    "body": "Yes, there is new node process created again when I kill and re-run the app.\nIf I open and kill app 5 times, I see 5 node process created (each time I\nopen app, and run child_process.fork() from renderer process, and kill app,\nnew node process is getting created and not getting destroyed.). As mention\nin issue, it gets killed when forked from main process but not from\nrenderer process.\n\nOn Sat, Sep 3, 2016 at 3:44 PM, Clément Nerma notifications@github.com\nwrote:\n\n> When you close this process, run your application again and close it, is\n> there still an electron process running ?\n> \n> —\n> You are receiving this because you authored the thread.\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/electron/electron/issues/7084#issuecomment-244568814,\n> or mute the thread\n> https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AQQ6aGnICAsZZySVgDgLnY-p1cJqRurBks5qmdw7gaJpZM4J0UE9\n> .\n"
