    "created_at": "2016-09-19T18:07:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-19T18:07:58Z",
    "body": "> How do I make sure to terminate all process created with child_process.fork() from renderer process? Would this be a bug in electron?\n\nOn macOS, I'm seeing the forked process stay around after quit regardless of if they are forked from the main or renderer process.\n\nBut it looks like node (6.3.0) behaves the same if I run `node index.js` with the following `index.js`:\n\n``` js\nrequire('child_process').fork('./forever.js')\nprocess.exit(0)\n```\n\nwith `forever.js` containing:\n\n``` js\nsetInterval(function () {\n  console.log('hey')\n}, 10000)\n```\n\nI see the forked `node` process hang around after the first process exits.\n"
